<br>
Power of fire:  Ya long camp, boring, typical VI... but it's easy.  I camped 16 hours straight for mine at blazing elementals.<br>
<br>
Torch: 1 group including a rogue, tank, cleric, chanter around lvl 60, pretty easy, &lt; 55 bring some extra friends, 1 hour job tops.<br>
<br>
PoA crown:  A little more difficult if you're not in a guild that can get to 7th isle.  Find a guild that has a necro camped out, pay them, if not crowns are getting cheaper on most servers.  Farm HG's for cash and buy one if needed.<br>
<br>
Slixin:  2 mages... easy job.<br>
<br>
Power of air:  2 mage job or get a shaman/tank/cleric friend to train the zone with her.<br>
<br>
Cloak:  A tad more difficult but easily remedied by either making a druid twink or having a tracker friend to with you.  If you're doing with druid/ranger twink camp your mage out in SK.  Find Quillmane, log mage and kill.  Also many people have posted good theories on Quillmane spawn, read those, they seem to be on target.<br>
<br>
Hate staff:  Got nothing to say here, it's a pain, this is one thing that *could* be changed imo<br>
<br>
Water staff:  Just keep killing PA, at least it tends to be more common than wiz staff.<br>
<br>
Tears of Errosi:  Rottgrime pull not that bad, just get someone that isn't KoS (like an SK) to pull out of town, FD and someone tag him.<br>
<br>
Nezi:  Go to -450, 2500 and kill everything in site, this one takes a while but it's not that bad.  Was about a 6 hour camp of a period of a couple days for me.<br>
<br>
<br>
I'll admit, while I did my epic there was times of frustration, but when I felt like that I tried to just focus on getting the easier stuff, eventually the more difficult items will come your way.  Just get to know guilds/people that do these things and help them out with epics/raids etc.  <br>
<br>
If you find it that hard.... don't do it, a game is supposed to be fun, but don't expect everything handed to you, especially an item of this magnitude.<br>
<br>
Good luck and keep sane. <p>Master Caldywen Lebeau <BR>
Level 60 Arch Mage <BR>
Echoes in Eternity <BR>
Rodcet Nife <BR>
"You want fries and a coke with that mod rod?" <BR>
