<br>
VI has tweaked so many epics, and yet done nearly nothing to the mage epic.  Seriously, I would be overjoyed if they just did something about quillmane.  Make a level 60 pegasus like qwinn in SK.  Get a lore no-drop trigger from something in PoA (off the other pegasui?)  Give trigger to pegasus, he goes into a rage and you gotta beat him up.  Triggered will despawn so gotta kill fast or else get another trigger.  And as a reward, he'll drop a cloak.  This encourages grouping and gives the shaft to all those druids and rangers who want to MQ it for you.  Leave the original in though so the option remains and so other classes that want it have a &quot;chance&quot;.<br>
<br>
Is that too much to ask?  After you've...<br>
Made the white scale no longer for the 9int/wis dam3 cloak so bards have no competition from casters.<br>
Made Trakanon triggerable for bards.<br>
Made Zordak triggerable in Skyfire for clerics.<br>
Made Venril Sather and Faydedar triggerable for druids.<br>
Put the Wraith of a Shissar on it's own timer for enchanters.<br>
Made Venril Sather triggerable for rangers.<br>
Changed the hand of maestro situation for warriors.<br>
Revamped the wizard epic so instead of cazic/tolapumj you  need the broken golem.<br>
<br>
From what i've gathered the 'change' to the earth staff might have helped some, it wasn't enough.<br>
<br>
And call me crazy, but I seem to remember the 'General's Quill' subquest to the rogue epic a LOT longer...requiring not just the 4 robes, but also 4 swords and 4 piercers... was I just dreaming this?<br>
